<p>You're entitled to a partial refund if you paid any application fees from April 2013 to March 2017 for your: 

<ul class="list list-bullet">
    <li>lasting power of attorney (LPA) for property and financial affairs, or LPA for health and welfare</li>
    <li>enduring power of attorney (EPA) - an earlier type of power of attorney</li> 
</ul>

<div class="panel panel-border-wide">
    <p>You only need to submit one claim, even if you made 2 LPAs or paid twice because of a mistake. Records 
    will be checked for all the fees you paid.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="heading-medium">Who can claim a refund</h2>

<ul class="list list-bullet">
    <li>The 'donor' - the person who made the LPA or EPA</li>
    <li>An 'attorney' - trusted by the donor and claiming on their behalf</li>
</ul>

<p>The refund is for the donor, even if someone else paid the fees for them.</P> 

<h2 class="heading-medium">How much you'll get</h2>

